# Test Zhao + Beetle-Headed Merchants Sacrifice Synergy
# Zhao, Ruthless Admiral: "Whenever you sacrifice another permanent, creatures you control get +1/+0 until end of turn"
# Beetle-Headed Merchants: "Whenever this creature attacks, you may sacrifice another creature or artifact. If you do, draw a card and put a +1/+1 counter on this creature."
# Expected: When Beetle attacks and sacrifices a creature:
# 1. Beetle draws a card and gets +1/+1 counter (5/4 -> 6/5)
# 2. Zhao's Mode$ Sacrificed triggers, giving +1/+0 to all creatures (Zhao 3/4 -> 4/4, Beetle 6/5 -> 7/5)
# Result: Zhao should be 4/4, Beetle should be 7/5

[metadata]
Name:Zhao + Beetle Sacrifice Synergy
Goal:Win
Turns:5
Difficulty:Easy

[state]
# Player 0 (AI) - starts with Zhao and Beetle on battlefield, Typhoid Rats to sacrifice
p0life=20
p0hand=Swamp
p0library=Mountain; Forest; Swamp; Island; Mountain
p0battlefield=Zhao, Ruthless Admiral; Beetle-Headed Merchants; Typhoid Rats; Mountain; Mountain; Swamp; Swamp

# Player 1 - opponent with minimal blockers
p1life=20
p1hand=Forest
p1library=Island; Island; Island; Island; Island
p1battlefield=Forest; Forest
